ation with him than from any other leader I have personally known. He is our model as a servant and follower of the Lord Jesus Christ of these things I testify in the name of Jesus Christ amen."

2) Cleaned transcription (with speaker labels):
President of the Quorum of the Twelve:
My dear brothers and sisters, we meet as we mourn the death of our beloved President Russell M. Nelson. I speak to you as the President of the Quorum of the Twelve, a position in which I have been sustained in our ward, stake, and general conferences for the past seven and a half years.

We now go forward with this semi-annual general conference, proceeding as planned with speakers and music assigned by President Nelson after months of preparation. The only additions are my introductory explanation and my speaking in place of President Nelson in the closing session on Sunday afternoon.

This is the first time in about 75 years that a church president has died a few days before a general conference. That has required us to plan how we could hold the vital leadership meetings in connection with general conference, as well as this general session, while scheduling his funeral as soon as possible.

President Nelson understood the value of general conference to provide direction to the Saints in the coming months. We honor him by following the planned conference schedule he approved.

In this time of grief we have already held a meeting to pay tribute to President Russell M. Nelson before our general conference meetings and have scheduled his funeral as soon as possible after conference. All of this has been done with the approval of the family of President Nelson and the Quorum of the Twelve.

Since all of us who have been assigned to speak in general conference would like to devote our assigned time to paying a personal tribute to President Nelson, we have asked that all conference speakers hold such tributes to a minimum, deferring elaborate tributes for the funeral, which we have already begun to plan.

My own brief tribute, suitable to this conference and to the tributes we have already paid, is this: I love Russell M. Nelson and have learned more about the gospel and gospel leadership from my long friendship and association with him than from any other leader I have personally known. He is our model as a servant and follower of the Lord Jesus Christ. Of these things I testify in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.

3) Extracted items

Key points:
- Announcement of the death of President Russell M. Nelson.
- Speaker: President of the Quorum of the Twelve (sustained in that role for ~7.5 years).
- Semi-annual general conference will proceed as planned with speakers and music as assigned by President Nelson.
- Additions to the schedule: the Quorum Presidents introductory explanation and his speaking in place of President Nelson in the Sunday closing session.
- First time in ~75 years a church president died days before conference, requiring coordination of leadership meetings and funeral timing.
- Tribute meeting held prior to conference; funeral scheduled with family and Quorum approval.
- Conference speakers asked to keep personal tributes brief and defer more elaborate tributes to the funeral.
- Speaker offered a brief personal tribute praising President Nelson as a model servant and follower of Jesus Christ.

Action items:
- Proceed with the semi-annual general conference as scheduled.
- All assigned conference speakers should keep personal tributes brief during conference sessions and defer longer tributes to the funeral.
- Continue coordinating leadership meetings and funeral arrangements with family and Quorum approval.

Decisions:
- To proceed with the scheduled general conference despite President Nelsons death.
- To add the Quorum Presidents introductory remarks and have him speak in place of President Nelson in the closing session.
- To schedule President Nelsons funeral as soon as possible after the conference, with the approval of his family and the Quorum of the Twelve.
- To request brief tributes during conference and reserve extended tributes for the funeral.

4) Concise summary (3 bullets):
- The President of the Quorum of the Twelve announced the passing of President Russell M. Nelson and confirmed the semi-annual general conference will proceed as planned.
- Funeral arrangements have been scheduled promptly after conference with family and Quorum approval; speakers were asked to keep tribute remarks brief during conference and defer longer tributes to the funeral.
- The Quorum President will provide introductory remarks and will speak in place of President Nelson in the closing session; he offered a brief personal tribute praising President Nelson's gospel leadership.

End of deliverable.
